10/10/2003
ANTALYA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and Greek counterpart George Papandreou announced on Thursday (9 October) the cancellation of Greek and Cypriot military exercises code-named ''Nikiforos'' and ''Toxotis'', as well as of Turkey's ''Tavros'' and ''Barbarosa'' exercises, scheduled to begin next year.
The move is seen as a good will gesture in light of the Athens Summer Olympics and as a sign of improved bilateral relations.
(ANA, MPA, Makfax - 09/10/03)
